track.name: Corinna
comments: As I've said other times on other tracks, what a wasted talent Taj turned out to be. It's strange how sometimes people's compasses just stop working and they seem to get lost in trivialities. ....Not meaning this particular song, which I like...

Anyone who's cut his teeth with Ry Cooder and vice versa... is worth an extended listen!

Taj blues at his best (first 3 albums). Bought this 2nd album back in 1968 when it came out and have never tired of hearing it over the years. Check out the first album "Taj Mahal" if you haven't already. Every track is a classic, especially Statesboro Blues (Jesse Ed Davis playing delicious slide guitar),  Leaving Trunk and Celebrated Walking Blues. One cool dude ...
